I don't care how many reports you make, captain,

679
00:44:50,776 --> 00:44:57,111
只要新的坐标是4131-2595  你明白了吗
just as long as the new coordinates are 4131-2795. Have you got that?

680
00:45:02,997 --> 00:45:04,954
嘿  这到底是怎么回事
Hey, what the hell's going on here?

681
00:45:05,124 --> 00:45:06,618
我们正在改变方向
We're changing directions.

682
00:45:11,297 --> 00:45:14,251
少校  如果我们不跳到我们计划的地方
Major, if we don't jump where we planned,

683
00:45:14,425 --> 00:45:16,299
我们将如何与抵抗联系起来
how will we link up with the Resistance?

684
00:45:16,469 --> 00:45:17,749
你让我担心
You let me worry about that.

685
00:45:17,928 --> 00:45:20,254
我在斯科普里有一个地址
I've got an address in Skopje.

686
00:45:20,431 --> 00:45:22,969
你和我会找到它的  Demchuk
You and I will find it, Demchuk.

687
00:45:28,147 --> 00:45:29,606
Vasco  他们要迟到了
They are running late, Vasco.

688
00:45:29,773 --> 00:45:31,932
他们会来的  我姐姐收到…
They'll be here. My sister received...

689
00:46:07,478 --> 00:46:10,016
出了问题  我得回斯科普里了
Something's gone wrong. I have to get back to Skopje.

690
00:46:10,189 --> 00:46:12,347
无论如何我们都得离开这里
We have to get out of here in any case.

691
00:46:16,070 --> 00:46:19,273
无论发生什么事  我都需要一个囚犯来审讯
Whatever happens, I need one prisoner for interrogation.

692
00:46:19,615 --> 00:46:21,109
我们要那六个
We'll take those six.

693
00:46:24,870 --> 00:46:26,530
你们这些人  投降
You men, surrender!

694
00:46:50,563 --> 00:46:53,232
我有你的囚犯审问  上尉
I have your prisoner for interrogation, captain.

695
00:46:53,774 --> 00:46:55,352
让他活着
Keep him alive.

696
00:47:53,626 --> 00:47:54,954
先生  请不要往下看
Don't look down, sir.

697
00:47:55,127 --> 00:47:56,787
看着他们就好像你恨他们一样
Look at them as if you hate them

698
00:47:56,962 --> 00:47:58,872
他们肯定你是南斯拉夫人
and they will be sure you are Yugoslav.

699
00:48:26,242 --> 00:48:28,993
对  阿瑞斯是战争之神
Yes? Ares is the god of war.

700
00:48:30,287 --> 00:48:32,743
我们都是他的孩子
And we are all his children.

701
00:48:32,915 --> 00:48:34,160
进来
Come in.

702
00:48:37,962 --> 00:48:39,753
站住  拿起他们的枪
Stand still. Take their guns.

703
00:48:39,922 --> 00:48:41,297
这到底是什么
Now, what the hell is this?

704
00:48:41,465 --> 00:48:43,026
保持安静  彼得  检查一下弹药
Keep quiet. Peter, check the ammunition.

705
00:48:45,052 --> 00:48:46,712
美国陆军  标准问题
U.S. Army, standard issue,

706
00:48:46,887 --> 00:48:49,461
45口径弹药  全新的
.45-calibre ammunition, brand-new.

707
00:48:49,640 --> 00:48:52,676
你在找谁  我已经给过你密码了
Who are you looking for? I already gave you the password.

708
00:48:52,852 --> 00:48:56,386
密码可能已经被那些被撕掉舌头的人折磨掉了
The password could have been tortured out of men who then had their tongues torn out.

709
00:48:56,564 --> 00:48:59,019
你在找谁  党派领袖
Who are you looking for? A partisan leader.

710
00:48:59,191 --> 00:49:01,861
缩写Y.V.
Initials Y.V.

711
00:49:03,696 --> 00:49:06,021
我是Yelena Vascovic
I am Yelena Vascovic.

712
00:49:06,490 --> 00:49:09,491
没有人知道你只有我的姓名首字母
No one else knew that you had only my initials.

713
00:49:09,660 --> 00:49:11,700
昨晚发生了什么事
What happened last night?

714
00:49:11,871 --> 00:49:15,037
嘿  看  我可以说得好些  没有那个炮指着我的头
Hey, look, I can talk a lot better without that cannon pointing at my head.

715
00:49:16,208 --> 00:49:18,450
对不起  对不起
Please, I'm sorry.

716
00:49:18,627 --> 00:49:20,537
我理解
I understand.

717
00:49:20,713 --> 00:49:23,251
我命令着陆区上空飞行
I ordered an overflight over the landing area.

718
00:49:23,424 --> 00:49:26,105
我只是预感到德国人在那里等着我们
I just had a hunch that maybe the Germans were there waiting for us.

719
00:49:26,218 --> 00:49:28,045
没有党派会把你交给德国人
No partisan would give you to the Germans.

720
00:49:28,220 --> 00:49:30,047
嘿  我没那么说
Hey, I didn't say that.

721
00:49:30,222 --> 00:49:33,971
好吧  我们接到命令  不管什么原因  我们没有联系
Okay, we had orders that, for whatever reason we didn't make any contact,

722
00:49:34,143 --> 00:49:36,219
我们是来这里的  我们到了
we were to come here. So here we are.

723
00:49:36,395 --> 00:49:38,886
那些想见你的人没有回来
The men that were supposed to meet you did not come back.

724
00:49:39,064 --> 00:49:41,022
我们整晚都没听到他们说的话
We have heard no word all night from them.

725
00:49:41,192 --> 00:49:43,647
最好假设他们被带走了
It's best to assume they were taken.

726
00:49:43,819 --> 00:49:45,563
其中一个是我弟弟
One of them was my brother.

727
00:49:48,741 --> 00:49:50,864
如果他们幸运的话  他们就有机会战斗了
If they were lucky, they had a chance to fight.

728
00:49:51,577 --> 00:49:54,282
看  我们能给海岸附近的英国潜艇发个口信吗
Look, can we get a message to the British submarine off the coast?

729
00:49:54,455 --> 00:49:56,531
是的  当然  告诉他们我们成功了
Yes, of course. Tell them we made it.

730
00:50:05,090 --> 00:50:07,842
鹰四狮一  鹰四狮一
Eagle Four to Lion One. Eagle Four to Lion One.

731
00:50:08,010 --> 00:50:09,290
你能读懂我吗
Can you read me?

732
00:50:09,470 --> 00:50:13,005
是的  这是狮子一号  请往前走
- Yes, this is Lion One. - Go ahead, please.

733
00:50:13,849 --> 00:50:18,310
这是老鹰四号  718-9.
This is Eagle Four. 7-187-9.

734
00:50:18,479 --> 00:50:18,979
192724
192724.

735
00:50:24,276 --> 00:50:26,233
来访者已经到了
The visitors have arrived.

736
00:50:26,403 --> 00:50:29,108
很好  我有一个来自伦敦霸王的信息
Very good. I have a message from Overlord in London.

737
00:50:29,281 --> 00:50:31,274
你能马上离开SK Opje吗
Can you get out of Sk opje at once?

738
00:50:31,450 --> 00:50:35,115
他们必须对你决定着陆地点的反应做出反应
They must be reacting to your decision to overfly the landing site.

739
00:50:35,287 --> 00:50:36,782
告诉我出了什么事
Tell me what's wrong.

740
00:50:36,956 --> 00:50:39,707
没什么不对的  我们正在路上
Nothing's wrong. We're on our way.

741
00:50:40,668 --> 00:50:41,913
肯定的
Affirmative.

742
00:50:42,086 --> 00:50:44,956
很好  再见
Very good. Cheerio.

743
00:50:47,299 --> 00:50:51,131
对不起  昨晚你弟弟来接我们
Look, I'm sorry your brother came to meet us last night.

744
00:50:51,303 --> 00:50:55,135
我的哥哥  上帝愿意  已经死了
My brother, God willing, is dead.

745
00:51:11,699 --> 00:51:13,027
他又失去知觉了
He's lost consciousness again.

746
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:15,240
是的  我能看到
Yes, I can see that.

747
00:51:15,411 --> 00:51:18,365
我让你查明Major Wright要袭击火车
I asked you to find out where Major Wright will attack the train

748
00:51:18,539 --> 00:51:21,291
经过数小时的审讯  你没有结果
and after hours of interrogation, you have no results.

749
00:51:21,458 --> 00:51:24,139
将军  请原谅我  但最好还是把火车挂起来
Forgive me, general. But would it not be better to hold up the train

750
00:51:24,170 --> 00:51:25,415
还是走另一条路
or take another route?

751
00:51:25,588 --> 00:51:28,339
我应该给F解释什么
What explanation am I supposed to give the f黨rer?

752
00:51:28,507 --> 00:51:30,796
我不能把他的部下从叛徒专业中解救出来
That I cannot save his men from a renegade major

753
00:51:30,968 --> 00:51:32,759
还有12个普通罪犯
and 12 common criminals?

754
00:51:45,608 --> 00:51:47,316
你想去那列火车吗
Where do you want to hit that train?

755
00:51:47,485 --> 00:51:50,688
这是我们穿越空旷国家的计划…
This is the plan We go through open country...

756
00:51:51,238 --> 00:51:53,694
我们在附近的火车上相遇
and we meet the train here, near Nish.

757
00:51:53,866 --> 00:51:57,116
在保加利亚边境以北20英里处有一个立交桥
There's an overpass about 20 miles north of the Bulgarian border,

758
00:51:57,286 --> 00:51:58,531
在Pirot附近
near Pirot.

759
00:51:58,704 --> 00:52:01,277
火车因等级下降而减慢速度
The train slows down there because of a grade.

760
00:52:01,457 --> 00:52:03,117
我训练了我的男人
And I've trained my men

761
00:52:03,292 --> 00:52:05,700
从立交桥上跳上这些移动的汽车
to jump on these moving cars from the overpass

762
00:52:05,878 --> 00:52:07,787
把这些纳粹分子赶走
to take out these Nazi hotshots.

763
00:52:07,963 --> 00:52:11,213
然后我会向我的人解释  如果他们有什么问题  我会告诉你的
Then I'll explain it to my men. If they have any problems, I'll let you know.

764
00:52:18,474 --> 00:52:20,550
Stern  我能为你做点什么
Well, what can I do for you, Stern?

765
00:52:20,726 --> 00:52:22,719
少校  有点糊涂了
The men are a little confused, major.

766
00:52:22,895 --> 00:52:24,519
哦  也许有点害怕吧
Oh, a little scared, maybe?

767
00:52:24,688 --> 00:52:27,061
嗯  很多事情都没有发生
Well, a lot of things have been happening that don't quite add up.

768
00:52:27,233 --> 00:52:29,233
首先  霍夫曼从那架飞机上跳了出来
First, Hoffman jumps out of that plane and bounces.

769
00:52:29,360 --> 00:52:31,685
霍夫曼在一次训练事故中丧生
Hoffman was killed in a training accident.

770
00:52:31,862 --> 00:52:34,899
只有你抓住了尸体和溜槽  才把他救出来
Only you grabbed the body and the chute and got him out of there.

771
00:52:35,074 --> 00:52:36,734
是的  那么我们不应该跳到我们应该去的地方
Yeah, then we don't jump where we're supposed to,

772
00:52:36,909 --> 00:52:39,151
我们不进入斯科普里  我们在山上蜿蜒
we don't go into Skopje, we wind up in the hills.

773
00:52:39,328 --> 00:52:42,448
如果你想和德国人一起跳下去在斯科普里散步
If you wanted to jump down with the Germans and walk in Skopje,

774
00:52:42,623 --> 00:52:43,868
你是我的客人  乔
you be my guest, Joe.

775
00:52:44,041 --> 00:52:45,500
怎么回事  少校
What the hell's going on, major?

776
00:52:47,336 --> 00:52:50,954
好的  你有权知道
All right. You're entitled to know.

777
00:52:51,131 --> 00:52:53,338
这次肮脏的打电话响了
There's a ringer in the Dirty Dozen this time.

778
00:52:55,719 --> 00:52:57,379
是的  腐烂了
That's right, something rotten.

779
00:52:57,555 --> 00:53:00,758
一个把我们都卖掉的犹大
A Judas who's selling us all out.

780
00:53:03,936 --> 00:53:05,456
难道它不是南斯拉夫人吗
Couldn't it be one of the Yugoslavians?

781
00:53:05,604 --> 00:53:09,472
不  南斯拉夫人没有切开霍夫曼的斜线
No, the Yugoslavs didn't slice Hoffman's chute line.

782
00:53:10,401 --> 00:53:13,604
这是我们的一个  离家乡很近
It's one of us, closer to home.

783
00:53:19,994 --> 00:53:21,618
对
Yes?

784
00:53:22,788 --> 00:53:24,615
贝尔格莱德  将军
Belgrade, general.

785
00:53:26,834 --> 00:53:28,743
李希特将军
General Richter.

786
00:53:30,462 --> 00:53:32,585
给我坐标
Give me the coordinates.

787
00:53:32,756 --> 00:53:35,923
立即通知柏林奥伯曼曼多
Notify Oberkommando Berlin immediately.

788
00:53:36,093 --> 00:53:39,213
不  没关系  我自己打电话
No, never mind, I will make the call myself.

789
00:53:57,865 --> 00:54:00,154
他们不到一小时前就在这里进攻了
They attacked here less than an hour ago.

790
00:54:00,326 --> 00:54:03,825
但是  先生  我们的信息是  他们将继续使用
But, sir, our information was that they would go on to Nish.

791
00:54:04,121 --> 00:54:05,746
这是正确的
That's right.

792
00:54:06,248 --> 00:54:09,664
少校莱特没有降落伞  我们预期他
Major Wright did not parachute in where we expected him.

793
00:54:09,835 --> 00:54:12,326
他没有攻击我们所期望的他
He didn't attack where we expected him.

794
00:54:12,505 --> 00:54:16,585
我怀疑他是否会攻击我们所期望的火车
I doubt very much if he'll attack the train where we expect him.

795
00:54:18,969 --> 00:54:20,927
让飞机15分钟后起飞
Get a plane ready to leave in 15 minutes.

796
00:54:21,514 --> 00:54:23,672
为Sofia提供航班信息
File flight information for Sofia.

797
00:54:33,484 --> 00:54:37,351
他死了  长官  是的  我能看见  上尉
He's dead, sir. Yes, I can see that, captain.

798
00:55:14,358 --> 00:55:16,351
我以为我们要穿越空旷的国家
I thought we were going through open country.

799
00:55:16,527 --> 00:55:18,603
我猜少校一直在改变主意
The major keeps changing his mind, I guess.

800
00:55:18,779 --> 00:55:21,317
你知道我在想什么吗  我不知道
You know what I been thinking? I got no idea.

801
00:55:21,490 --> 00:55:23,399
我以前从未有过中尉
I never had a lieutenant before.

802
00:55:41,844 --> 00:55:44,845
你今天要把尸体带到Pirot埋葬和归还吗
You're taking the body to Pirot for burial and returning today?

803
00:55:45,431 --> 00:55:47,507
是死者的遗愿
Was last wish of deceased.

804
00:55:48,100 --> 00:55:50,852
你的试卷看起来很整齐  等一下
Your papers seem to be in order. Wait a minute.

805
00:55:56,025 --> 00:55:57,685
你来自哪个村庄
What village are you from?

806
00:55:57,860 --> 00:55:59,936
库马诺沃  先生  离这儿只有几英里远
Kumanovo, sir. Just few miles from here.

807
00:56:00,112 --> 00:56:02,437
我知道那个该死的村庄在哪里
I know where the damn village is.

808
00:56:04,658 --> 00:56:08,608
有多少游击队员藏匿在那里  等待杀害德国士兵
How many partisans are hiding there, waiting to murder German soldiers?

809
00:56:09,705 --> 00:56:11,745
没有  长官  我知道
None, sir, that I know of.

810
00:56:11,916 --> 00:56:13,493
说谎
Lying.

811
00:56:14,668 --> 00:56:16,460
该死的马其顿人
Damned Macedonians.

812
00:56:18,964 --> 00:56:21,716
在哀悼中  你呢
In mourning, are you?

813
00:56:21,884 --> 00:56:26,131
亲爱的死去的灵魂  是的
For a dear departed soul, yes.

814
00:56:34,396 --> 00:56:37,563
你几乎可以是德国人了
You could almost be German.

815
00:56:38,275 --> 00:56:41,312
北欧  嗯  纯的
Nordic, hm? Pure.

816
00:56:45,658 --> 00:56:49,109
纯在这个国家的猪
Pure in this country of swine.

817
00:56:52,164 --> 00:56:53,742
打开棺材
Open the coffin.

818
00:56:53,916 --> 00:56:57,036
我想看看你是否在边境走私任何东西…
I want to see if you're smuggling anything across the border...

819
00:56:57,211 --> 00:56:58,491
除了死者
besides the dead.

820
00:56:58,671 --> 00:57:01,078
长官  神圣服务结束了
Sir, it was closed after holy service.

821
00:57:01,257 --> 00:57:03,664
在这一生中  有…然后我会打开它
In this life, there is... Then I will open it.

822
00:57:03,843 --> 00:57:05,123
是啊
Yeah?

823
00:57:34,874 --> 00:57:37,447
好吧  里面一定有电话
All right, there must be a phone in there.

824
00:58:17,750 --> 00:58:20,585
贝尔格莱德正试图回击  他们一定过去了
Belgrade is trying to call back. They must have got through.

825
00:58:20,753 --> 00:58:22,911
好的  五分钟后我们就离开这里
All right, we'll be out of here in five minutes.

826
00:58:23,088 --> 00:58:24,915
半小时后天就黑了
And it'll be dark in a half-hour.

827
00:59:26,944 --> 00:59:28,818
正规军一路  对吗  中士
Regular Army all the way, right, sergeant?

828
00:59:29,280 --> 00:59:30,608
是的  先生
Yes, sir.

829
00:59:30,781 --> 00:59:33,153
看  我得到了穆兹的狗标签
Look, I got Mu馿z's dog tags.

830
00:59:33,325 --> 00:59:35,365
如果有什么事情发生在我身上…
If anything should happen to me...

831
00:59:35,536 --> 00:59:37,410
我希望你能把这些标签拿回来  如果可以的话
I want you to get those tags back, if you can.

832
00:59:37,580 --> 00:59:38,611
是的  先生
Yes, sir.

833
00:59:38,789 --> 00:59:40,912
现在  我们应该袭击边境上的火车
Now, we're supposed to attack the train on the border.

834
00:59:41,083 --> 00:59:45,994
真正的目标  Sofia以东
The real target? East of Sofia.

835
00:59:54,513 --> 00:59:56,470
所以我在学校的最后一年
So my last year in school,

836
00:59:56,640 --> 01:00:00,508
我要么结婚  要么尝试外国服务
I was either gonna get married or try for the Foreign Service.

837
01:00:01,145 --> 01:00:03,184
一定是一个艰难的决定
Must have been a hell of a tough decision.

838
01:00:04,857 --> 01:00:08,641
不要笑  我可能是个很好的妻子…
Don't laugh. I might have been a very good wife...

839
01:00:08,819 --> 01:00:11,606
安德鲁是一位相当聪明的外国服务官员
andlor a reasonably bright Foreign Service officer.

840
01:00:12,114 --> 01:00:14,522
可能是  你还不能吗
Might have been? Can't you still be?

841
01:00:15,409 --> 01:00:18,695
我认为未来不远  乔
I don't think that far ahead in the future, Joe.

842
01:00:18,871 --> 01:00:20,780
不再了
Not anymore.

843
01:00:22,541 --> 01:00:25,661
你呢  没有战后的计划
What about you? No postwar plans?

844
01:00:27,713 --> 01:00:30,382
我在战争中已经很久了
I've been in the war a long time.

845
